{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c7457a20-297a-4243-84bf-fa14406c56e4","agentId":"a2f3e3cbee2119600","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are performing end-to-end integration validation (Task 9) for the `project-reader` Claude Code plugin at `~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/`.\n\n## Goal\n\nVerify the complete plugin file structure and all unit tests pass. This is a validation-only task — do NOT modify any source files.\n\n## Step 1: Confirm all required files exist\n\n```bash\nfind ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader -type f | sort\n```\n\nExpected files (verify ALL of these exist):\n```\nagents/project-detector.md\nagents/structure-explorer.md\ncommands/read.md\nhooks/hooks.json\nhooks/session_start.py\nhooks/tests/test_session_start.py\nplugin.json\nskills/core/entry-finder.md\nskills/lang/ios.md\ntemplates/analysis-index.md\ntemplates/project-map.md\n```\n\n## Step 2: Run all unit tests\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader\npytest hooks/tests/test_session_start.py -v\n```\n\nExpected: 15/15 PASSED\n\n## Step 3: Verify plugin.json format\n\n```bash\ncat ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/plugin.json\n```\n\nExpected: valid JSON with name, version, description, author fields.\n\n## Step 4: Verify hooks.json format\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('$HOME/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/hooks/hooks.json')); print('valid JSON'); print('SessionStart hook:', 'SessionStart' in d['hooks'])\"\n```\n\nExpected: `valid JSON` and `SessionStart hook: True`\n\n## Step 5: Test SessionStart script on a real project\n\nFind an iOS project and test the hook:\n\n```bash\n# Find iOS project\nTEST_PROJECT=$(find ~ -maxdepth 6 -name \"*.xcodeproj\" -type d 2>/dev/null | grep -v DerivedData | grep -v Pods | head -1 | xargs dirname 2>/dev/null)\n\nif [ -z \"$TEST_PROJECT\" ]; then\n  echo \"No iOS project found, using plugin-dev as fallback\"\n  TEST_PROJECT=~/Desktop/AiStudy/claude-learn/plugin-dev\nfi\n\necho \"=== Testing with project: $TEST_PROJECT ===\"\n\n# Compute key and clear old cache\nKEY=$(cd \"$TEST_PROJECT\" && python3 -c \"import hashlib,os; cwd=os.getcwd(); print(f'{os.path.basename(cwd)}-{hashlib.md5(cwd.encode()).hexdigest()[:8]}')\")\necho \"Project key: $KEY\"\nrm -rf ~/.claude/analyses/$KEY\n\n# First run (cache miss — should scan)\necho \"\"\necho \"--- First run (should scan) ---\"\ncd \"$TEST_PROJECT\" && python3 ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/hooks/session_start.py\n\n# Second run (cache hit — should load cache)\necho \"\"\necho \"--- Second run (should load cache) ---\"\ncd \"$TEST_PROJECT\" && python3 ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/hooks/session_start.py\n\n# Show INDEX.md\necho \"\"\necho \"--- INDEX.md content ---\"\ncat ~/.claude/analyses/$KEY/INDEX.md\n```\n\n## Step 6: Test non-project directory (silent exit)\n\n```bash\ncd /tmp && python3 ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader/hooks/session_start.py\necho \"Exit code: $?\"\n```\n\nExpected: no output, exit code 0\n\n## Step 7: Verify git log\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader && git log --oneline\n```\n\nExpected: multiple commits showing the implementation history.\n\n## Step 8: Final commit (if any uncommitted changes exist)\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.claude/plugins/local/project-reader\ngit status\n# If clean, no action needed\n# If dirty, commit with:\n# git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 1 complete - project-reader plugin core scaffold with iOS support\"\n```\n\n## Report Format\n\nReport one of:\n- **DONE** — all checks passed, include test output and smoke test output\n- **DONE_WITH_CONCERNS** — mostly passing but something to flag\n- **BLOCKED** — critical failure, explain what failed\n\nInclude:\n1. File list output (Step 1)\n2. Test results (Step 2)\n3. Smoke test output (Step 5)\n4. Git log (Step 7)"},"uuid":"2ea88ec6-e60e-40be-b268-9dcc789b2642","timestamp":"2026-03-17T04:04:13.238Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/xpeng/Desk